<Layout title="The Golden Ratio in Nature">
	<h1>The Golden Ratio in Nature</h1>
	<p class="date">Published on May 15, 2023</p>
	<img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2e/FibonacciSpiral.svg/640px-FibonacciSpiral.svg.png" alt="Golden Ratio Spiral" class="feature-image">
	<article>
		<p>The golden ratio, approximately 1.618, is a mathematical concept that appears frequently in nature and has been used in art and architecture for centuries. This article explores its presence in the natural world and its significance in various fields.</p>
		<h2>What is the Golden Ratio?</h2>
		<p>The golden ratio, denoted by the Greek letter φ (phi), is an irrational number that satisfies the equation:</p>
		<div class="math-equation">
			φ = 1 + 1/φ
		</div>
		<p>This equation leads to the approximate value of 1.61803398875...</p>
		<h2>The Golden Ratio in Nature</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Spiral galaxies</li>
			<li>Nautilus shells</li>
			<li>Sunflower seed patterns</li>
			<li>Pine cone spirals</li>
			<li>Human body proportions</li>
		</ul>
		<p>These natural occurrences of the golden ratio contribute to the perception of beauty and balance in nature.</p>
	</article>
</Layout>

